messageBody:
Yes, I agree that this is confusing.  I noticed that and some other 'misspellings' in the QS manual, but in the end just chalked them up to differences in accent.  But I agree with you, given my west-coast American accent, "busy" is "bizI"

(it has been quiet here!  I am as guilty as anyone.)

oliver

On 02 Dec 2006, at 20:33, pete_a90 wrote:

I'm confused about this letter because according to both the manual
and
http://home.earthlink.net/~sbartok1632/quik/qprojects/qdict/qdic_e/b.htm

busy = bizi

I would have thought it would be pronounced

bizI instead (i.e. with letter #27 in place of the y).
